@NODE Requirements "mris: Requirements"

                       @{b}Requirements for running mris@{ub}

   Mris requires AmigaOS 3.0 (V39) or newer to run. You will also need a
   "reasonably" fast system to actually enjoy the game. I have developed
   mris on a standard  A3000  running AmigaOS 3.1 (V40.68). On a 4 color
   screen it runs  fine, but on a 8 color screen it is  often too  slow,
   but still playable. Mris actually  looks  quite  okay with  8 colors,
   while msit gets a weird palette.

   Due to the extremely  slow  Amiga  gfx  hardware,  I  assume  that  a
   standard A3000 equipped with a gfx board can run mris in full color.

   If locale.library  is  not  available, mris will  fall back  to using
   german  (since  the  german  strings  are  built into  the  program).
   However, it will first look for an english manual before  trying  the
   german manual. Other manuals are ignored.

   Before complaining about  the obvious fact that  Mr.  Do clones exist
   that run on a standard A500 in 32 colors, consider that mris is fully
   system  compliant,  hardware independent,  and runs in  an  intuition
   window. If this is not what you want, use one these hardware-banging,
   system-killing, "crash on anything but 68000" games.

@ENDNODE

